# =============================================================================
# .gitignore -- WAM Training Disable
# =============================================================================
#
# Why this file exists:
#   PowerShell projects accumulate a few classes of generated artifacts that we
#   never want in source control: test result files, coverage reports, locally
#   resolved configuration files (the kind that hold connection strings), and
#   editor scratch files. Listing them here keeps the repo clean and avoids the
#   embarrassing class of bug where someone commits a config file containing a
#   real production credential.
#
# Convention: each block has a one-line header explaining WHAT it covers and a
# short comment explaining WHY before the patterns themselves.
# =============================================================================


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Pester test artifacts
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Pester writes NUnit/JUnit XML and code-coverage XML side-by-side with the
# tests when run with -OutputFile or via the project's tests/PesterConfiguration.
# Those files are generated on every test run, get uploaded as CI artifacts,
# and have no business in git.
TestResults*.xml
coverage*.xml
PesterCoverage*.xml
*.Tests.xml


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local resolved configuration
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The module's configuration resolver looks at a user-local config file before
# falling back to the shipped default. That local file is, by design, where the
# real SQL connection string and other environment-specific values live. NEVER
# commit it.
WamTrainingDisable.local.config.psd1
config.local.psd1
*.local.psd1


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Per-run output (logs the script itself produces)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# A developer running the script (or DropInCompat tests) locally will produce
# output files under output/ or out/. These are run artifacts; the canonical
# fixtures live under tests/fixtures and are checked in deliberately.
output/
out/
LockoutUsers_*.log
LockoutList_*.txt


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PowerShell working files
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# *.bak: PowerShell ISE and a few editors leave .bak files when saving over an
# existing file. *.ps1xml.bak: same for type/format files. Catch them all.
*.bak
*.tmp


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Editor / IDE
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# VS Code's .vscode folder may contain user-local launch settings or paths to
# private credentials. We deliberately do NOT track it; if a developer wants
# to share editor settings, they should commit a sample as .vscode.example.
.vscode/
.vs/
*.swp
*.swo
.idea/


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OS-generated noise
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Build / publish output
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# If we ever wire up a build that publishes the module to a local feed (the
# CONTRIBUTING.md "future work" section), it will land in build/ or publish/.
# Pre-emptively ignored so a future contributor doesn't accidentally commit a
# nupkg containing every file in the repo.
build/
publish/
*.nupkg
